auto generate multiple collors
create a gradient pallete instead of complete random
option to change each colour
save palette to local Storage

<!-- User Interface -->
1. Color display
    - divs to display the generated colors.
        - Hover effect to display buttons 
        - Text Element to display the current color code and change color when clicked.
        - 
    - Button to add or remove div's.

2. Button to favorite palletes.
    - 
    
3. Button to Save the pallete to local storage.
    - take pallete divs info.
    - take info on the colors in the div.
    - save the info in an archive.

<!-- Color generation algorithm: function to generate color gradient when activated. -->
 1. getRandomHue 
     - Generates a random base color in hex format.

 2. getComplementaryHue
     - Calculate the oposite color of the base color (complementary hue).

 3.  getGradient
     - Take the number of color display div's in the page and assign to a variable.
     - Calculate the gradient of colors between the base color and the oposite color, with the number of divs being the number of colors in the gradient.
     - Convert colors to rgb.
     - Assign each color to each div in order.

